7
 III(7; s.l.: 1, no stub; 2, no stub;
6, stub after 3/fols. 19r-25v )

handDesc.handNote:
- ጵ has the 6th order marker set up on
                       the vertical stroke at the top, oriented to the left (e.g., fol. 7vb
                       l.7);

- the upper horizontal stroke of መ ሠ ወ
                       (esp. መ), in the 1st order, is slanted to the
                       left;

- መ, in the 1st and 2nd orders, has
                       the right loop which does not rest on the ruled
                       line;

- ሎ has the loop and the horizontal
                       stroke marking the 7th order almost at the top, not in the
                       middle;

- the number ፬ is slightly triangular
                       and down wards-oriented (e.g., fol.
                       59ra);
